Description: The following statement contains a magic number: return lines                  .SkipWhile(x => !x.Contains("public symbols"))                  .Skip(2)                  .TakeWhile(x => !String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(x))                  .Select(x => x.Trim().Split(' '))                  .Select(x => new { Address = x[0]' Name = x[1].Substring(1) })                  .Where(x => !x.Name.StartsWith("?"))                  .Select(x => x.Name)                  .ToList();
